    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Goldberg may provide interesting insights to a Western reader about religious extremism in Pakistan and Afghanistan, but he ignores the cause of its spread. During the cold war, the West financed and supported the proliferation of religious schools in order to sustain the Afghan jihad against a onetime ''evil Soviet Empire.'' Immediately after the Soviet withdrawal, rather than help create stable institutions, the West washed its hands of Afghanistan and left Pakistan with the baggage.</p>
        <p>Akbar S. Babar  Islamabad, Pakistan</p>
      </block>
